%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% General guidelines for cover letters:
%
% 0. The cover letter must fit on a single page. 
%
% 1. If the resume is the interview, the cover letter is the
% pre-interview hand shake and introduction. Keep it brief, but personal. 
% Highlight the things about yourself that you want your PI to know, but don't
% brag. Skip the flattery. Be sincere.
% 
% 2. You can gamble with a flashy cover letter that will stand out, or have a
% more plain, professional looking one. Whatever your design choices, your
% cover letter must be easy to read, with a clean look.
% 
% 3. The cover letter consists of four sections:
% 	I. Introduction
% 	II. Your unique qualifications for the position
% 	III. Your most proud accomplishments that are relative to the position
%	IV. Closing
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
